6 — Development setup — step-by-step
Prerequisites:
- Node >= 18, npm >= 9
- MongoDB instance (Atlas or local)

Local quickstart:
1) Clone the repo
   git clone https://github.com/customcoder245/backend-tbd.git
   cd backend-tbd

2) Copy env template and fill variables
   cp .env.example .env
   # Edit .env and provide required values (MONGODB_URL, JWT_SECRET, etc.)

3) Install dependencies
   npm install

4) Start dev server
   npm run dev
   # dev = nodemon -r dotenv/config src/index.js

5) Health check
   curl http://localhost:8000/
   # Expected: { success: true, message: "API is working 🚀" }

6) Useful scripts (package.json)
- npm start — production-like start (node src/index.js)
- npm run dev — development with nodemon
- npm run lint — run eslint

Notes:
- If running on Vercel, ensure process.env.VERCEL is set so that index.js does not call listen (app exported for serverless).

