8 — Database models — schemas & important fields
This section lists the major models and the fields you will interact with most often. File paths are approximate — open src/models/*.model.js for exact schemas.

8.1 User (src/models/user.model.js)
- Fields:
  - _id (ObjectId)
  - email (String, unique, indexed)
  - password (String, hashed)
  - role (String enum: superAdmin, admin, leader, manager, employee)
  - orgName (String)
  - adminId (ObjectId referencing user)
  - firstName, lastName
  - department
  - profileImage (URL)
  - isEmailVerified (Boolean)
  - emailVerificationToken, emailVerificationExpires
  - resetPasswordToken, resetPasswordExpires
  - invitationToken (for guest invites)
  - profileCompleted (Boolean)
  - notificationPreferences (Object)
  - lastAssessmentScore, classification
- Methods:
  - generateAccessToken() -> returns JWT signed with JWT_SECRET (exp ~3h)

Indexes: invitationToken, resetPasswordToken, emailVerificationToken, role, orgName

8.2 Invitation (src/models/invitation.model.js)
- Fields:
  - token, token1 (String) — support for alternate token field
  - email (String)
  - invitedBy (user id)
  - role, department, orgName
  - used (Boolean)
  - expiredAt (Date)

Usage: employeeAccess middleware searches invitation by token or token1 and checks expiry/used flags.

8.3 Question
- Fields: id, orgName, text, type (single/multi/scale/text), options, weight, domain, tags, createdBy

8.4 Assessment / EmployeeAssessment / SubmittedAssessment
- Assessment stores template/metadata, participants, status, assigned stakeholders
- SubmittedAssessment/Response stores snapshot of answers per question with timestamps and optional score

8.5 Response
- Fields: assessmentId, respondent (user or guest), answers: [ { questionId, value, score } ], createdAt

Notes: Review index definitions in each model; they guide query performance for exports and dashboard aggregations.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9 — Authentication & token flows (detailed)
9.1 JWT-based auth
- Users log in with POST /api/v1/auth/login
- Controller validates credentials and returns JWT token and user info
- Tokens included in Authorization: Bearer <token> header for protected routes
- Tokens should be stored on the client side securely (httpOnly cookies recommended)

9.2 Invite / guest flows
- Invite tokens allow a guest/employee to access assessment without registering
- Two middlewares implement this:
  - flexibleProtect: accepts session JWT or invite token (header or cookie) and sets req.user or req.employee accordingly
  - employeeAccess: strict invite-mode — token required (x-invite-token header or query param)
- Invitations include used/expired flags — controllers should mark used=true when required

9.3 Token expiration and refresh
- JWT tokens have expiry — refresh approach is not implemented explicitly in the repo (consider adding refresh tokens if needed)

Security recommendations:
- Never commit JWT secret to repo
- Prefer short-lived tokens for admin flows and single-use tokens for invites
- Log suspicious token reuse or repeated token attempts (possible sharing/leak)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10 — Middlewares and their behavior
10.1 auth.middleware.js
- protect(req,res,next): verify Authorization header -> find user -> attach req.user
- flexibleProtect(req,res,next): first check Authorization header or cookie; if no session token, check invite token in x-invite-token or cookie; attach req.user or req.employee
- restrictTo(...roles): returns middleware that checks req.user.role

10.2 employee.middleware.js
- employeeAccess: validates invite token parameter/header -> finds Invitation -> checks used/expiry -> sets req.employee

10.3 multer.middleware.js
- upload (image files) -> disk storage to os.tmpdir() (or /tmp on Vercel)
- excelUpload -> used for bulk imports
- validateImageSize ensures image min 10KB and max 4MB

10.4 csvUpload.middleware.js
- Parses CSV to JS objects for bulk invitation imports; controller handles creation logic

10.5 role.middleware.js
- Small helpers to map roles and enforce role-specific logic

Operational notes:
- Always ensure temp files are removed from disk after processing to avoid filling /tmp
- For large uploads, consider streaming or offloading to direct-to-cloud uploads (pre-signed S3 URLs)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11 — Routes & endpoints — full reference with examples
Base path: /api/v1

A) Auth & User routes
- POST /auth/register
  Body: { email, password, firstName?, lastName?, orgName? }
  Response: newly created user (without password)

- POST /auth/login
  Body: { email, password }
  Response: { token, user }

- POST /auth/logout
  Clears cookie or server session

- GET /auth/me
  flexibleProtect -> returns current session or guest

- POST /auth/send-invitation (protect)
  Body: { email, role, orgName, department, expiresAt? }

- POST /auth/send-bulk-invitation (protect)
  multipart/form-data: file=invite.xlsx or invite.csv

B) Assessment
- GET /assessment/start
  Returns meta required to start assessment (templates, config)

- POST /assessment/start (protect)
  Create assessment draft and participants

- POST /assessment/:assessmentId/submit (protect)
  Accepts completion and persists SubmittedAssessment

- GET /assessment/history (protect)
  Returns user's past assessments

C) Employee Assessment (invite)
- POST /employee-assessment/start (employeeAccess)
  Body: { token or header } -> returns questions and assessment instance

- POST /employee-assessment/:assessmentId/submit/:token (employeeAccess)
  Body: { answers: [...] } -> saves responses and marks invitation used if applicable

D) Questions
- GET /questions/all (protect)
- POST /questions/upload (protect + excelUpload.single('file')) -> bulk import
- POST /questions/multiple -> seed multiple questions

E) Responses & Exports
- POST /responses (flexibleProtect) -> save or update responses
- GET /responses/:assessmentId -> fetch responses
- GET /responses/:assessmentId/export -> generate Excel and return download
- GET /responses/organization/:orgName/export -> org-level Excel

F) Dashboard & Reports
- GET /dashboard/export-pdf (protect) -> returns PDF (puppeteer)
- GET /dashboard/preview-pdf-report -> returns HTML preview

G) Organization
- CRUD endpoints for departments and org metadata (protect + restrictTo admin)

H) Contact
- POST /contact -> public contact form that triggers email or ticket

Endpoint example (curl) — login
curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/auth/login" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"email":"admin@example.com","password":"Password123"}'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
12 — File uploads, storage and exports
12.1 Upload handling
- multer with diskStorage writes files to os.tmpdir() locally and /tmp when deployed serverless
- Controllers should validate file types/mime and sizes
- After processing, files should be uploaded to Cloudinary or S3 and local temp files deleted

12.2 Export generation
- Excel: exceljs/xlsx/json2xls — produce workbook and either stream to response or store and return URL
- PDF: controllers use Puppeteer to render HTML + CSS and call page.pdf(). Use pdf-lib to post-process if needed

12.3 Performance considerations
- For large datasets, stream or chunk exports
- Offload heavy export generation to a worker/queue with persisted job state

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
13 — Background jobs, cron, and long-running tasks
13.1 Cron in src/index.js
- Schedules '* * * * *' for deleting expired/unverified users every minute (only when index.js runs)
- Also contains index-drop fix for assessments collection — review before running on prod

13.2 Recommendation
- Move scheduled tasks to a worker or an external scheduler
- Use Redis + BullMQ or similar for job queues (export generation, email jobs, cleanup tasks)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
14 — Deployment & production checklist (Vercel + alternatives)
14.1 Vercel (serverless)
- Set VERCEL=true in env so index.js does not call listen
- Confirm Puppeteer works with @sparticuz/chromium on Vercel build
- Use /tmp for temporary files and ensure cleanup
- Move cron/cleanup tasks to separate hosted runner

14.2 Docker / container deployment
- Use Dockerfile to build node image
- Run node src/index.js with proper envs
- Provision separate worker containers for scheduled jobs

14.3 Security & infra
- Use HTTPS and HSTS
- Ensure environment secrets are stored securely (Vercel environment, AWS Secrets Manager, or similar)
- Firewall and IP restrictions for DB access (Atlas allowlist)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
15 — Observability, logging & error handling
- Structured logging recommended (pino or winston)
- Centralize error handler in src/app.js to format API errors
- Capture unhandledRejection and uncaughtException and exit gracefully after logging
- Add request metrics and APM (Sentry, Datadog) for monitoring PDF/Export latency

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
16 — Testing, QA & CI recommendations
- Add unit tests (Jest) for utilities and model methods
- Add integration tests (Supertest) for critical endpoints (auth, invite, submit)
- CI pipeline (GitHub Actions): install, lint, test on PRs
- Add sample database fixtures for tests (use in-memory mongo or test DB)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
17 — Onboarding checklist (first 24 hours)
1) Read this PDF and open the key files (index.js, app.js, auth.controller.js)
2) Create .env from .env.example and run npm run dev
3) Register test user and test login
4) Create an invitation and run the employee assessment flow end-to-end
5) Upload a sample Excel for bulk invitation and test parsing
6) Generate an export (small org) and validate PDF/Excel output
7) Run linter and tests

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
18 — Troubleshooting guide — common issues & fixes
18.1 Mongo connection errors
- Verify MONGODB_URL and network access
- For SRV errors, confirm DNS and correct connection string

18.2 Invalid/expired JWT
- Check JWT_SECRET and token expiry
- Create a new token via login if required

18.3 Invitation/token not found
- Confirm whether token is stored in token or token1
- Check used flag and expiry

18.4 File upload problems on Vercel
- Ensure usage of /tmp and that files are removed after processing

18.5 Puppeteer/Chromium failures
- Confirm @sparticuz/chromium is included and compatible with runtime
- Increase memory/time limits or run in a dedicated container if heavy

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
19 — Security checklist
- Do not commit secrets
- Enforce input validation and sanitize inputs
- Add rate-limiting for auth endpoints
- Use HTTPS and secure cookies
- Limit exposure of invite tokens (prefer headers over URL)
- Periodically audit npm dependencies

